1
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:15,433
Your daughter is lucky that
she didn't meet her mother.

2
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:16,967
You're a beast!

3
00:00:17,033 --> 00:00:18,733
Don't involve my child in this!

4
00:00:21,533 --> 00:00:23,533
That's Doctor Charles Marfori.

5
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:24,767
How may I help you, Mookie?

6
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:29,800
Can you tell me my illnesses
since I was a child?

7
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:32,300
You weren't sick when
you were a child.

8
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:35,367
It's time to forget
about the memories.

9
00:00:35,467 --> 00:00:37,267
So I can be free from the past.

10
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:39,867
It's a muscle relaxant
for animals.

11
00:00:39,933 --> 00:00:43,033
But if it's used in people,
it can cause paralysis.

12
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:45,400
Promise me you'll be careful.

13
00:00:45,467 --> 00:00:46,533
I will.

14
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,467
I talked to Mookie yesterday.

15
00:00:48,533 --> 00:00:51,633
She was asking about
her medical history.

16
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:54,167
Obet, go back to the house now.

17
00:00:54,233 --> 00:00:54,867
Hurry!

18
00:01:33,733 --> 00:01:35,100
Years pass by so fast.

19
00:01:36,367 --> 00:01:37,100
I know.

20
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:41,333
17 years feels like yesterday.

21
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:48,400
There's something
I'm not telling you.

22
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:51,700
What is it?

23
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:57,567
For a long time,
it hasn't left my mind.

24
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,967
What if Kayla was alive?

25
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:07,400
Me, too, Emma.

26
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:11,333
I remember Kayla...

27
00:02:13,167 --> 00:02:14,533
whenever
I see a baby girl.

28
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:20,167
I know I'm just giving
myself a hard time.

29
00:02:21,033 --> 00:02:23,033
But I can't help but think.

30
00:02:23,867 --> 00:02:27,833
What if we weren't
there that day?

31
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:30,200
What if we were in
a different place?

32
00:02:30,267 --> 00:02:33,267
What if one detail changed?

33
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:37,567
But we can no longer
change the past.

34
00:02:40,133 --> 00:02:42,100
We can only do something...

35
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:45,867
about the present
and the future.

36
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:52,733
Dan, thank you for always
being there by my side.

37
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:58,667
You let me grieve
for a long time.

38
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,100
You've always been patient.

39
00:03:04,667 --> 00:03:07,033
We're life partners, Emma.

40
00:03:08,167 --> 00:03:10,133
I'll always be by your side.

41
00:03:14,633 --> 00:03:17,400
And now that I've said
goodbye to Mookie,

42
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:24,467
I'm also ready to bury all the
painful memories of Baby Kayla.

43
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:47,733
It's been 17 years
since I last saw her.

44
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:50,300
That's when we graduated
from medical school.

45
00:04:50,367 --> 00:04:53,200
Class of 2007.

46
00:04:53,267 --> 00:04:55,667
My birth year.

47
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:57,133
Exactly.

48
00:05:38,267 --> 00:05:38,867
Danilo?

49
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:40,933
Emma?

50
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:46,667
Wait. You look familiar.

51
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:48,633
Bukoy.

52
00:05:49,267 --> 00:05:50,767
- Oh, yeah.
- Bukoy.

53
00:05:51,767 --> 00:05:52,467
How's life?

54
00:05:53,467 --> 00:05:54,900
We're doing well. How are you?

55
00:05:54,967 --> 00:05:56,133
I'm okay.

56
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:57,367
How about you, guys?

57
00:05:57,433 --> 00:06:00,600
We haven't seen each other
since the landslide.

58
00:06:00,667 --> 00:06:03,000
My children and I went back
to Siquijor.

59
00:06:03,067 --> 00:06:05,300
I'm glad you and your
family are safe.

60
00:06:06,467 --> 00:06:08,133
How's your baby?

61
00:06:08,233 --> 00:06:09,300
I bet she's all grown up now.

62
00:06:13,267 --> 00:06:14,533
No, Bukoy.

63
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:17,267
Our child has been dead
for 17 years now.

64
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:19,400
She died during the landslide.

65
00:06:21,567 --> 00:06:22,867
That's impossible.

66
00:06:22,933 --> 00:06:24,600
I saw her that day.

67
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:54,433
Your reflexes are hyperactive.

68
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:57,800
And this indicates that
you might have an injury

69
00:06:57,867 --> 00:07:00,533
or damage in your spinal cord.

70
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,900
That's why you've lost
your legs' muscle function.

71
00:07:02,967 --> 00:07:05,767
Mommy, why did I get paralyzed?

72
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:06,967
I don't know either.

73
00:07:07,033 --> 00:07:10,200
But it looks like your condition
is acting out again.

74
00:07:10,267 --> 00:07:11,700
You're getting worse.

75
00:07:14,833 --> 00:07:17,933
Your leg will get amputated
if it gets worse.

76
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:21,467
This is pistachio!

77
00:07:22,033 --> 00:07:23,233
Are you stupid?

78
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:25,467
Mookie is allergic to peanuts!

79
00:07:27,167 --> 00:07:28,933
Considering how much
you've eaten,

80
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:31,333
you should've suffered from
severe throat tension

81
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:35,000
if you're allergic to pistachio.

82
00:07:35,067 --> 00:07:37,933
I suggest you discuss this
incident with her doctor

83
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:41,333
because I don't think
she's allergic to pistachios.

84
00:07:46,033 --> 00:07:47,867
What really is your illness?

85
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:50,800
Mom said I have
an autoimmune disease.

86
00:07:50,867 --> 00:07:52,500
And leukemia.

87
00:07:52,567 --> 00:07:53,733
With all the illnesses
you have,

88
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:56,533
why isn't your mom bringing
you to another doctor?

89
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,067
What for? I'm a doctor.

90
00:07:58,133 --> 00:07:59,333
I'm your pediatrician

91
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:02,400
from three to four months old
until five years old.

92
00:08:02,467 --> 00:08:03,533
I'm telling you,

93
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,600
you don't have any serious
medical condition.

94
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,133
Doc Charles was right.

95
00:08:11,567 --> 00:08:14,467
I was a healthy child.
I wasn't sick.

96
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:17,600
Olivia is your mom, right?

97
00:08:17,667 --> 00:08:18,933
Yes.

98
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:22,567
I remember, she requested
for all your medical records.

99
00:08:23,267 --> 00:08:25,567
I never saw her again
after that day.

100
00:08:27,733 --> 00:08:29,767
How could you just stand
there and do nothing?

101
00:08:29,833 --> 00:08:32,300
We should bring Mookie
to the hospital.

102
00:08:32,367 --> 00:08:34,333
So that she can get checked up.

103
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:36,900
I know better what
my child needs.

104
00:08:38,033 --> 00:08:40,833
And I'm never bringing
her to the hospital.

105
00:09:59,533 --> 00:10:00,467
Mookie, what are...

106
00:10:15,733 --> 00:10:16,333
Mookie...

107
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,867
I can explain everything.

108
00:10:21,067 --> 00:10:23,300
I called Doc Charles.

109
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:30,233
That's why I looked
at my records.

110
00:10:30,933 --> 00:10:37,133
Because he told me I wasn't
sick when I was a child.

111
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:48,100
Doc Charles was wrong.

112
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,567
He couldn't diagnose
your illness right.

113
00:10:51,633 --> 00:10:54,033
That's why I didn't bring
you back to his clinic.

114
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:58,100
When I talked to him, he
was so sure I was healthy.

115
00:10:58,167 --> 00:11:01,633
That I was a healthy kid.

116
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:04,200
Of course, he will say that!

117
00:11:04,267 --> 00:11:07,067
Because he's protecting
his reputation!

118
00:11:09,767 --> 00:11:12,133
Then how can you explain
this, Mommy?

119
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:15,267
It says here I am a healthy kid.

120
00:11:15,333 --> 00:11:16,833
Healthy kid, Mookie.

121
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:19,767
Maria Angela Caparas.
Healthy kid.

122
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,100
How?

123
00:11:22,167 --> 00:11:23,400
Go on, Mommy.

124
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:24,800
Explain.

125
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:29,067
These records are proof

126
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:31,667
that Doc Charles
is negligent and incompetent.

127
00:11:32,433 --> 00:11:34,433
That's why I kept these records.

128
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:35,900
I wanted to sue him.

129
00:11:35,967 --> 00:11:37,200
But I realized,

130
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:41,033
why would I waste my time
in court?

131
00:11:42,567 --> 00:11:45,767
I chose to care for you, Mookie.

132
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:49,433
All my life, you've been
telling me I'm sick.

133
00:11:50,767 --> 00:11:53,733
And then I saw these videos.

134
00:11:55,033 --> 00:11:57,400
I was healthy all along!

135
00:11:57,467 --> 00:12:00,767
And this is the first time
I've seen these videos.

136
00:12:01,433 --> 00:12:04,400
Mommy, why did you
keep this from me?

137
00:12:04,467 --> 00:12:05,600
I don't understand!

138
00:12:05,667 --> 00:12:07,233
Mookie, you don't understand.

139
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:09,133
I really don't understand,
Mommy!

140
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:14,133
Because I've been locked up
in this house all my life!

141
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:18,533
- Mookie.
- I only want to get better.

142
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:23,467
But why do I feel like
you're stealing my life from me?

143
00:12:23,533 --> 00:12:25,200
Why, Mommy?

144
00:12:25,267 --> 00:12:28,800
I kept those photos
and videos from you

145
00:12:29,633 --> 00:12:31,133
because I didn't want you to see

146
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:33,300
that you were healthy
once in your life!

147
00:12:34,167 --> 00:12:38,700
That you could do things
that normal kids outside do.

148
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:43,433
Because I know
you'll get depressed

149
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:45,800
if you see those photos
and videos!

150
00:12:45,867 --> 00:12:48,867
You'll be saddened by
your condition, Mookie!

151
00:12:48,967 --> 00:12:51,167
I was just protecting you.

152
00:12:51,233 --> 00:12:53,067
That's all I wanted to do.

153
00:12:53,133 --> 00:12:55,367
I wanted to protect you!

154
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:04,300
Mookie.

155
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:08,533
I will only ask
you this once.

156
00:13:11,433 --> 00:13:13,700
Am I really sick?

157
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:29,533
You saw Baby Kayla?

158
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:31,433
Yes. I'm sure of it.

159
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:32,700
A woman was carrying her.

160
00:13:32,767 --> 00:13:34,500
She went out of your house.

161
00:13:34,567 --> 00:13:35,267
Are you sure?
Do you know her?

162
00:13:36,067 --> 00:13:37,333
Do you know the woman?

163
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:38,233
I don't.

164
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,167
But I'm sure she
wasn't from here.

165
00:13:41,233 --> 00:13:43,367
The day of the landslide
was the first time I saw her.

166
00:13:43,433 --> 00:13:44,400
That's why I remember

167
00:13:44,467 --> 00:13:45,567
she looked like she wasn't
a resident here.

168
00:13:45,633 --> 00:13:46,933
Do you remember her face?

169
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:50,100
Sorry, it was a long time ago.

170
00:13:51,267 --> 00:13:53,867
Maybe you're mistaken.

171
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:55,267
No, Danilo.

172
00:13:55,367 --> 00:13:57,233
I'm sure it wasn't Emma.

173
00:13:59,133 --> 00:14:01,533
Dan, someone took Kayla.

174
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,100
Someone took her.

175
00:14:04,133 --> 00:14:05,767
What happened to
your baby is tragic.

176
00:14:06,567 --> 00:14:09,767
Danilo, I'll give you
my number if you need help.

177
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:10,433
Okay.

178
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:11,900
You can call me anytime.

179
00:14:13,067 --> 00:14:13,900
Is it correct?

180
00:14:17,933 --> 00:14:18,567
Thank you.

181
00:14:19,367 --> 00:14:20,900
I'll go ahead.

182
00:14:20,967 --> 00:14:22,567
I hope you find your baby.

183
00:14:25,867 --> 00:14:28,800
Kayla is alive, Dan!

184
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:30,333
Baby Kayla is alive!

185
00:14:39,633 --> 00:14:40,567
What, Mommy?

186
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:43,333
Yes.

187
00:14:45,267 --> 00:14:47,600
You are sick.

188
00:14:50,733 --> 00:14:52,133
What do you think?

189
00:14:53,867 --> 00:14:56,467
That I'm just making
your illnesses up?

190
00:15:01,967 --> 00:15:03,467
I don't know.

191
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:06,133
I don't know, Mommy.

192
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:08,733
I don't know.
I really don't know.

193
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:11,367
I don't understand.

194
00:15:11,433 --> 00:15:15,200
I'm confused.
I'm so confused.

195
00:15:17,267 --> 00:15:18,033
Mookie.

196
00:15:18,967 --> 00:15:21,800
Mookie, don't you believe me?

197
00:15:24,033 --> 00:15:26,000
I really don't know, Mommy.

198
00:15:27,667 --> 00:15:29,833
Right now, I'm so confused.

199
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:32,867
I don't know what to believe in.

200
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:36,567
You often insist that I'm sick.

201
00:15:36,667 --> 00:15:38,900
That I've been sick
since I was a child.

202
00:15:38,967 --> 00:15:40,467
But I don't understand.

203
00:15:40,533 --> 00:15:42,567
Why do the videos
show otherwise?

204
00:15:42,633 --> 00:15:44,533
How can you explain
the pictures?

205
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:47,133
Why was I like this?

206
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:49,100
Why do I look healthy?

207
00:15:49,167 --> 00:15:50,700
I don't understand.

208
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:53,367
These videos...

209
00:15:56,367 --> 00:16:00,167
were a year after your
symptoms appeared.

210
00:16:02,233 --> 00:16:03,133
And here.

211
00:16:05,467 --> 00:16:07,433
I have proof to show you.

212
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:12,567
Because I took a video of when
your symptoms first appeared.

213
00:16:13,533 --> 00:16:16,800
These videos was before
you got sick, Mookie.

214
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:34,467
- Mommy, catch me!
- Mookie!

215
00:16:34,533 --> 00:16:36,600
Hurry! I'm almost near you!

216
00:16:36,667 --> 00:16:37,833
Run!

217
00:16:37,900 --> 00:16:39,033
There!

218
00:16:40,267 --> 00:16:42,200
I got you!

219
00:16:43,333 --> 00:16:45,000
Do you still want to play?

220
00:16:46,567 --> 00:16:47,667
Are you tired already?

221
00:16:48,133 --> 00:16:50,967
My baby got tired already.

222
00:16:51,033 --> 00:16:53,600
Let me see your face.

223
00:16:56,067 --> 00:16:58,833
Mookie, why is your
nose bleeding?

224
00:16:59,433 --> 00:17:00,533
Nanny, call the driver!

225
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,967
We'll go to the hospital!

226
00:17:16,567 --> 00:17:17,833
Dan, what's the matter?

227
00:17:19,267 --> 00:17:23,133
I'm thinking about
what Bukoy said.

228
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,967
I remember he used
to be a drunkard.

229
00:17:25,033 --> 00:17:26,633
I'm not so convinced.

230
00:17:27,867 --> 00:17:30,533
He saw Baby Kayla alive.

231
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:33,333
A woman took her
out of our house.

232
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:35,400
Baby Kayla is alive.

233
00:17:35,467 --> 00:17:39,700
I have reason to hope
because someone saw her alive.

234
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:41,633
Emma, I don't want
you to get hurt.

235
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:45,367
Emma, I'm just protecting you.

236
00:17:45,433 --> 00:17:46,467
I don't need protection.

237
00:17:46,533 --> 00:17:48,300
What I need is support.

238
00:17:49,133 --> 00:17:51,600
I can feel that Kayla is alive.

239
00:17:51,667 --> 00:17:53,033
Baby Kayla is alive.

240
00:17:55,667 --> 00:17:58,433
Jun, please drive.

241
00:18:04,867 --> 00:18:07,433
Your nosebleed
became persistent.

242
00:18:09,633 --> 00:18:15,867
I observed you and discovered
you had leukemia.

243
00:18:18,767 --> 00:18:20,967
But you became weaker.

244
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:24,867
I observed you some more,

245
00:18:24,933 --> 00:18:30,500
and then I discovered again that
you had an autoimmune disease.

246
00:18:34,067 --> 00:18:35,933
You discovered, Mommy?

247
00:18:38,133 --> 00:18:44,533
So, it means no other
doctor diagnosed my sickness.

248
00:18:47,767 --> 00:18:49,567
I'm a doctor, Mookie.

249
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:52,833
I saw all the symptoms.

250
00:18:53,733 --> 00:18:57,633
But more than being a doctor,
I am your mother.

251
00:18:57,733 --> 00:19:00,600
I know and feel
that you're sick.

252
00:19:02,733 --> 00:19:05,100
I had your blood samples
checked in a lab,

253
00:19:05,167 --> 00:19:07,700
and, true enough,
all my diagnoses were correct.

254
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:21,167
Are you really a doctor?

255
00:19:29,300 --> 00:19:31,233
I'm insulted, Mookie!

256
00:19:34,100 --> 00:19:37,333
Are you questioning
my being a doctor?

257
00:19:39,033 --> 00:19:40,367
I don't know, Mommy.

258
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:45,333
That's what I heard.

259
00:19:46,067 --> 00:19:46,900
Who did you hear it from?

260
00:19:48,033 --> 00:19:49,333
From Astrid?

261
00:19:49,867 --> 00:19:52,500
Or from that darn laundress?

262
00:19:52,567 --> 00:19:56,967
It's not important anymore
who I heard it from.

263
00:19:59,433 --> 00:20:01,467
I also saw the article online.

264
00:20:01,567 --> 00:20:03,667
My gosh, Mookie!

265
00:20:03,733 --> 00:20:05,200
Article online?

266
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:07,567
Those are lies!

267
00:20:08,533 --> 00:20:12,633
People who hate and
envy me made that up!

268
00:20:13,533 --> 00:20:14,500
Well, Mommy,

269
00:20:16,333 --> 00:20:18,467
if you really are a doctor,

270
00:20:19,933 --> 00:20:24,000
why are you giving me a muscle
relaxant for animals?

271
00:20:27,633 --> 00:20:31,300
Mommy, I saw the vial
for Canixidol.

272
00:20:31,367 --> 00:20:33,000
And it's for animals!

273
00:20:33,067 --> 00:20:36,333
Why are you administering
a veterinary drug to me?

274
00:20:36,433 --> 00:20:40,133
Mookie, why do you keep
asking questions?

275
00:20:42,267 --> 00:20:44,167
There are two types
of Canixidol.

276
00:20:44,233 --> 00:20:47,267
One for animals
and one for humans.

277
00:20:48,867 --> 00:20:52,200
Of course, I'm giving
you the one for humans.

278
00:20:52,267 --> 00:20:53,933
What do you think of me?

279
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:00,667
Mookie...

280
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:05,000
I don't know where
this information

281
00:21:05,067 --> 00:21:05,800
about Canixidol comes from.

282
00:21:05,867 --> 00:21:07,300
But please!

283
00:21:08,633 --> 00:21:11,067
Find out the truth next time!

284
00:21:12,300 --> 00:21:15,033
Because I will never
do that to you, dear.

285
00:21:15,733 --> 00:21:19,833
I will never administer
any veterinary drugs to you!

286
00:21:21,300 --> 00:21:22,800
I will never do that!

287
00:21:23,833 --> 00:21:25,833
I won't.

288
00:22:05,567 --> 00:22:06,500
Mookie!

289
00:22:06,967 --> 00:22:08,200
Why are you still here?

290
00:22:08,267 --> 00:22:10,000
Why are you still up?

291
00:22:10,067 --> 00:22:10,967
Come on.

292
00:22:11,033 --> 00:22:14,067
Flor, do you see
a medicine vial?

293
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:16,367
The one Mommy always
injects on me?

294
00:22:16,467 --> 00:22:17,433
Vial?

295
00:22:18,100 --> 00:22:20,200
Is that the tiny bottle?

296
00:22:20,267 --> 00:22:23,033
I saw it while cleaning earlier.

297
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:24,033
Why?

298
00:22:24,100 --> 00:22:25,267
Where is it?

299
00:22:25,333 --> 00:22:27,400
Ma'am Olive has it.

300
00:22:27,467 --> 00:22:31,000
She saw me holding it
when she came earlier.

301
00:22:31,067 --> 00:22:32,500
So she took it.

302
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:35,967
Let's go.

303
00:22:39,367 --> 00:22:39,867
Flor?

304
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:41,833
Why does it smell smoke?

305
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:43,500
Smoke?

306
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:45,700
Yeah, you're right.

307
00:22:51,433 --> 00:22:52,300
That's Ma'am Olive.

308
00:23:00,867 --> 00:23:04,067
Flor, can you hand me
my binoculars?

309
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:05,467
Wait.

310
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:12,100
Here.

311
00:23:13,633 --> 00:23:14,733
Thank you, Flor.

312
00:23:27,967 --> 00:23:29,633
What are you doing, Mommy?

313
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:43,200
What?

314
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:46,367
Baby Kayla is alive?

315
00:23:47,833 --> 00:23:48,367
Dear!

316
00:23:48,933 --> 00:23:51,667
Mom, you're like Emma.

317
00:23:51,733 --> 00:23:52,667
You believe easily.

318
00:23:53,333 --> 00:23:54,833
Why not?

319
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,633
I want to believe her.

320
00:23:57,267 --> 00:23:58,900
She's a mother.

321
00:23:58,967 --> 00:24:01,567
She can feel if Baby Kayla
is alive.

322
00:24:02,700 --> 00:24:03,733
Really, dear?

323
00:24:04,367 --> 00:24:05,233
Yes, Mom.

324
00:24:06,067 --> 00:24:07,967
Fine, I agree with you.

325
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:13,733
If Baby Kayla was the baby
that woman was carrying,

326
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:16,433
the one Bukoy saw,

327
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:18,467
if she saved Baby Kayla,

328
00:24:18,533 --> 00:24:20,433
she should've looked for you.

329
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:22,333
And returned the baby to you.

330
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:23,933
Exactly, Mom.

331
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,467
But have you also thought,

332
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:35,333
what if that woman went there
to abduct kids?

333
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:38,367
What if she's a member
of a syndicate?

334
00:24:38,433 --> 00:24:43,633
What if she takes advantage of
situations like that to kidnap?

335
00:24:43,700 --> 00:24:47,833
My God. I hope I'm wrong.

336
00:24:47,900 --> 00:24:48,733
Mom.

337
00:24:50,167 --> 00:24:51,967
What if Kayla got kidnapped?

338
00:24:53,033 --> 00:24:57,400
And weren't you hit that night?

339
00:25:07,167 --> 00:25:11,000
What if that woman did that?

340
00:25:11,667 --> 00:25:13,600
What if she deliberately
ran you over?

341
00:25:15,833 --> 00:25:18,600
And if a syndicate took Kayla,

342
00:25:18,667 --> 00:25:20,800
she's probably one of those kids
they use

343
00:25:20,867 --> 00:25:23,067
to beg for money on the street,

344
00:25:23,133 --> 00:25:27,400
or maybe she's being abused by
the crazy woman who took her.

345
00:25:27,467 --> 00:25:29,633
I hope not, Mom.

346
00:25:29,700 --> 00:25:32,600
Please go back to
Barangay Pinagkaisahan.

347
00:25:32,667 --> 00:25:33,900
Find that woman.

348
00:25:33,967 --> 00:25:34,900
Bring back my granddaughter.

349
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,633
Bring her back here.

350
00:25:44,333 --> 00:25:46,467
I think it's time for you
to tell Mookie the truth.

351
00:25:46,533 --> 00:25:47,967
She's starting to notice it.

352
00:25:48,033 --> 00:25:52,467
And please, stop giving
her medicines she doesn't need.

353
00:25:53,433 --> 00:25:56,033
I'm not asking for your opinion.

354
00:25:56,100 --> 00:25:58,533
If your mom isn't a doctor,

355
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:02,500
you must get checked by a real
doctor to hear the truth.

356
00:26:02,567 --> 00:26:04,600
How's my sister Olive?

357
00:26:04,667 --> 00:26:07,000
I'm already in Manila.

358
00:26:07,067 --> 00:26:08,167
The hell, I care.

359
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:10,800
I want to get my share
in our ancestral house.

360
00:26:10,900 --> 00:26:13,333
Never, ever try me, Jade!

361
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:16,500
I'm on my way there, Mang Ando.

362
00:26:16,567 --> 00:26:18,667
I'll probably be there
in one hour.

363
00:26:18,733 --> 00:26:20,633
Jade might arrive before I do.

364
00:26:20,700 --> 00:26:24,100
She has a key to daddy's vault,
where the land title is kept.

365
00:26:24,933 --> 00:26:25,567
Here.

366
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:28,000
This is where I saw
the car of the woman

367
00:26:28,067 --> 00:26:29,367
who took your child stop.
